# 🛒 Bazzar — Complete Project Deep Dive

## 1. What is Bazzar? What Problem Does It Solve? Who Uses It?

**Bazzar** (also styled as *Modrn*) is a **full-stack online bookstore** — a niche e-commerce platform purpose-built to sell books in Pakistan.

### The Problem It Solves
It provides a clean, user-friendly way to browse and purchase books online, organized by genre (Fiction, Academic, Islamic, Children, Self Help), with a simple checkout flow using Cash-on-Delivery (COD) style order placement. Think of it as a lightweight, custom-built alternative to Daraz or Kitaboon, specifically for books.

### Who Uses It?
| Persona | What They Do |
|---|---|
| **Guest / Visitor** | Browses books, categories, and landing page |
| **Registered Customer** | Creates an account, shops, checks out, tracks their orders |
| **Admin (Zoha Malik)** | Manages the product catalog and monitors/fulfills all orders |

### Real-World Use Case
A customer visits the site → browses book categories → adds books to cart → checks out by entering their name, phone, and delivery address → receives an order confirmation receipt on-screen. The admin then logs into their dashboard to see the order and update its status (Pending → Processing → Shipping → Delivered).

